 Albeit light.  The style I use (misty gloom) adds little damage (+2, +3) and saps alot of end.  But if I don't use it, I more often then not hit with my offhand weap for 10-13, primary for 19-24, but hardly ever both, if I DO hit with both weaps, killing mobs is only average, as I hit for around 30.  I feel like I've wasted my time so far training in celtic dual because the styles suck.  Once again, I know I'm low level but it seems to suck compared to the many other melee classes I have played, and I've played them all just about.  So to sum it all up:  Is it going to get better or just get worse?  Am I going to be forced to respecc to blunt or rid myself of CD just to be effective?  I really like the look and feel of the class, I'd hate to have to go back to my friar to feel like I'm getting somewhere.  This all may be just because I'm in a new realm and a new class so please give me some advice. <p>Vardord - 9 Blademaster (Merlin)<br>
