<br>
The style (Misty Gloom) you are using is the Starter CD style. All Starter styles are weak with high end costs. You're probably better off using one of your taunts (Fire Blade or Squall) because even though it has a defense penalty, you'll do more damage. CD styles should be used for reactionary and positional attacks only. The anytime styles are inferior to the base weapon anytime styles. You should have the evade based Blinding Rain style. You should use that as often as you can. Right now, you're probably only dual swinging about 30% of the time. Once your CD gets higher, you should double swing a lot more which adds a lot to your damage.<br>
<br>
